<br>
That being said, the reality is we are less useful in Velious than kunark. So are all other casters. It is tough for wizzys to get groups, but it is tough for anyone that is not a warrior, cleric, chanter, or rogue/monk. The funny part is that the main reason I ever get in a non-guild group is for snare......Nobody evacs after 55 unless evaccing to zone in. You lose the camp and the tanks have to walk.<br>
<br>
I am sure Verant, even though I give them a hard time, understand the issues with wizards, but I don't think they know how to fix them. Truth be told I don't think we know how to do it in a way that is not unbalancing. (I still vote for wizzys toget a cannibalize type spell)<br>
<br>
I think they are currently realizing that there are 3 main classes required and two others desired so that leaves 7 classes that have trouble finding groups. This is a fundamental balance problem that I assume they want to try to find a single thing that can help all the 7. Until they try the broad strokes, don't look for any details.<br>
<br>
I have always been vocal and a tad pessimistic but in the current situation and their recent trys at fixing broad strokes (resistances in skyshrine) I think we should all have a little patience and try to have as much fun as we can with what we have. I also say expect nothing and you will not be disappointed.<br>
<br>
Hugs all<br>
<br>
