<br>
Scenario 1 -<br>
Two decently balanced groups, I'm the only wiz in attendance and am in Group 2.  Each group has 2 melee's of close to equal damage output and either other caster classes filling in the holes.  Taking place in Kael on arena mobs (Troopers, Lego's, Adjutants and such).  Starting when the mob is about 20% down, I'll start laying in Draught of Fire, get in maybe 6 nukes at a reasonable pace so as not to aggro the mob.  NO EXP<br>
<br>
Scenario 2 -<br>
Same situation, only this time I wait til mob is about 35% down and start laying in Tears of Solusek rain spell, 2 draught of fire, another rain, 2 draught of fire and maybe 3 or more nukes to finish it off.  Even with the occasional resist, that's an assload of damage...NO EXP<br>
<br>
Scenario 3 -<br>
Same situation, medding through because I'm OOM trying to get a damn xp kill, guess what....we get EXP.<br>
<br>
WTF is up with that??<br>
<br>
As i've said, this isn't an isolated case.  I've tested these findings in PoG, Juggas, Hate, wherever there's at least a 2 group raid going on, and the results are always the same, there is more of a chance that my group will get the EXP if I just sit on my ass and let the rogue/monk/warrior whack away and get us the xp kill.  The more I nuke, the less our chances.  I know this doesn't make sense and quite frankly it really pisses me off, but that's the way it is.<br>
<br>
Disgruntled 56th wizard of Xegony<br>
