<br>
The simple truth of it is this: MoBs are getting more uber, MoBs are dropping more uber items, uber items have a direct increase in how much damage a melee character will do, items that do not generate effects do *ahem* dick all for casters, we (all of us, mages necros wizards) cast for the same damage as if we were naked, at least an enchanter's charisma affects how long their charms last...<br>
<br>
Items are getting better, hence melee classes are getting better, items are getting better, our spells are not. The more expansions the greater the rift will grow until items have a direct correlation to the casting of spells (cast time, recast time, dmg, mana cost, size of area of effect, resistance, fizzling, etc)<br>
<br>
The saving grace of casters may be that they can solo, which is fine and good, until you hit the higher 50s.<br>
<br>
No one seems to have mentioned tears of druzzil, which is 1200-1800dmg for 380 mana, the chance at resistance is high, yes... but you never hit for less than 1200 when the mob is tashed (albeit it is only useful on a solo mob), odd that I didnt see anything mentioned.<br>
<br>
If the 2 new uber lures could hit any mob they'd be just barely balanced, though we'd still never compete with melee on velious mobs. Why the hell didnt Verant impliment the percentage of HPs damage spells which would have worked and been balanced?<br>
<br>
All casters have complaints, all casting based classes need something new implimented to become balance, with perhaps the exception of enchanters and clerics whom's primary purpose does not involve dealing damage. The above mentioned about equiptment is just one possible solution.<br>
<br>
The biggest question to ask, is how do we make the point to Verant in such a way that they will act?<br>
<br>
Tawanos Planeswalker<br>
57th High Elf Evoker<br>
Paradigm Nocturne<br>
Tholuxe Paells<br>
<br>
&quot;It's not about winning or loosing, it's about beating everyone else&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umysthyl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mysthyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 132<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/17/01 6:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> wizards</span><hr size=1> 60 wizard KSing a group with a 55+ warrior and monk is NOT going to happen. Even chain nuking the wizard won't be able to match the damage of the monk+warrior not to mention what the other 4 people were doing. Look at a series of pulls and the wizard's damage falls even lower. From tests i've done on wizards in exp groups i'd say the wizard is lucky to do 20% the damage of the warrior+monk combo in long term damage.<br>
<br>
On the matter of not nuking to get kills i've noticed this too. In certain group situations group has a better chance to get kill when i (60wiz) DON'T nuke. My theory is the kill is given to the group with the highest average level on the hate list. So a wizard who nukes but then falls to the end of the hate list hurts the groups average and therefore hinders group in terms of getting exp. One thing that seams to work is to throw a few draughts in at the very end so mob dies with you very high on the list therefore bringing up the group hate average and therefore giving a better chance of getting the kill.<br>
<br>
The reason wizards are so disgusted by the way things are is becaues they are so opposite of what we expected them to be. We all have pre-concieved notions of what wizards are and that isn't what verant gave us; In fact it wasn't what they advertised to us either. As a wizard i want one thing, to be a major contributor in dealing damage. <br>
<br>
Another thing is that the game has changed drastically improving classes so far past the wizard that we have been left behind. I remember back in Lguk as a 49 wizard grouped with tanks that, if they were well equiped, would duel yaks. I could burn down mobs fast on an overpull (IC is about 1/4 dars hps) and my long term damage wasn't too far behind what the tank's was. In seb at lvl 59 a wizard can barely burn down one of the easiest of mobs if you can call it a burn. Wizard would probably be using draught of ice (731 damage) so it would take quite a while assuming the wizard didn't get pasted.<br>
<br>
Why should warriors be so good at taking damage (something wizards can't do at all) and still do more then two times the damage of a wizard? Don't tell me its utility a warrior through procs and unlimited effects can: levitate, invis, see invis, eb, summon bandages, heal, regen, str buff, ac buff, haste buff, atk buff, hp buff, damage shield, tash, snare, slow. Thats a heck of alot of utility for a non casting pure mele class. <br>
<br>
One last thing before i wrap up. Tanks can be drastically increased with equipmen. A tanks damage output can be more then trippled by aquiring good weapons and haste items. Seeing as these items are always increasing warriors (and all tanks) will always be increasing their damage and ac. Casters can't increase their damage output by equipment (we've seen no increase in caster damage since release) so its inevitable that tanks will far outdamage casters (situation we are in today). <br>
<br>
Well thats enough rambling for me.<br>
<br>
Mysthyl<br>
